# Discord Meeting Reminder Bot 🤖

A FastAPI-powered Discord bot that sends automatic meeting reminders to your team.

## Features ✨

- ⏰ Automatic meeting reminders based on schedule
- 👥 Team-specific mentions
- 🔄 Runs 24/7 on Railway
- 🌐 REST API endpoints for monitoring
- 🛡️ Environment variable configuration

## Setup 🚀

### 1. Discord Bot Setup

1. Go to [Discord Developer Portal](https://discord.com/developers/applications)
2. Create a new application
3. Go to "Bot" section and create a bot
4. **IMPORTANT**: Click "Regenerate Token" (your old token was exposed)
5. Copy the new token
6. Enable these Privileged Gateway Intents:
   - Message Content Intent
   - Server Members Intent

### 2. Get Channel ID

1. Enable Developer Mode in Discord (Settings → Advanced → Developer Mode)
2. Right-click on your target channel
3. Click "Copy Channel ID"

### 3. Deploy to Railway

1. Push this code to GitHub
2. Go to [Railway](https://railway.app/)
3. Create new project from GitHub repo
4. Add Environment Variables:
   - `DISCORD_TOKEN`: Your new Discord bot token
   - `CHANNEL_ID`: Your Discord channel ID
5. Deploy!

## Environment Variables 🔐

Create a `.env` file locally (already in `.gitignore`):

```env
DISCORD_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
CHANNEL_ID=1491453600822460655
PORT=8000
```

**⚠️ NEVER commit the `.env` file to Git!**

## API Endpoints 📡

- `GET /` - Bot status and info
- `GET /health` - Health check (for Railway)
- `GET /schedule` - View meeting schedule
- `GET /status` - Detailed bot status

## Meeting Schedule 📅

The bot checks every 30 seconds and sends reminders when:
- Current day matches the meeting's days
- Current time matches the meeting's time
- The reminder hasn't been sent yet today

